Isolation:
\f1\b0  Transactions are processed independently and securely, order does not matter. A low level of isolation enables many users to access the data simultaneously, however this also increases the possibilities of concurrency effects (e.g., dirty reads or lost updates). On the other hand, a high level of isolation reduces these chances of concurrency effects, but also uses more system resources and transactions blocking each other. Source: {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Isolation_%28database_systems%29"}}{\fldrslt \cf5 Wikipedia}} \cb1 \
